{"relationshipsSections":[{"kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper"],"title":"Inherits From","type":"inheritsFrom"},{"kind":"relationships","title":"Conforming Types","type":"conformingTypes","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"StaticMutexProtocol"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib14PointerWrapperP","text":"PointerWrapper","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"overview","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Prior to GLib 2.32, GStaticMutex had the significant advantage"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that it doesn’t need to be created at run-time, but can be defined","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"at compile-time. Since 2.32, ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","type":"reference"},{"text":" can be statically allocated","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"as well, and GStaticMutex has been deprecated.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is a version of our "},{"code":"give_me_next_number()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" example using"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a GStaticMutex:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["  int","  give_me_next_number (void)","  {","    static int current_number = 0;","    int ret_val;","    static GStaticMutex mutex = G_STATIC_MUTEX_INIT;","","    g_static_mutex_lock (&mutex);","    ret_val = current_number = calc_next_number (current_number);","    g_static_mutex_unlock (&mutex);","","    return ret_val;","  }"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":null},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Sometimes you would like to dynamically create a mutex. If you don’t","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"want to require prior calling to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_thread_init()"},{"text":", because your code","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"should also be usable in non-threaded programs, you are not able to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"use ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_mutex_new()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and thus "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":", as that requires a prior call to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_thread_init()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". In these cases you can also use a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It must be initialized with ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_static_mutex_init()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" before using it"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"and freed with with "},{"code":"g_static_mutex_free()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" when not needed anymore to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"free up any allocated resources."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Even though ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","type":"reference"},{"text":" is not opaque, it should only be used with","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the following functions, as it is defined differently on different"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"platforms.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"All of the g_static_mutex_* functions apart from","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_static_mutex_get_mutex()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" can also be used even if "},{"code":"g_thread_init()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"has not yet been called. Then they do nothing, apart from"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_static_mutex_trylock()"},{"text":" which does nothing but returning ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All of the g_static_mutex_* functions are actually macros. Apart from"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"taking their addresses, you can however use them as if they were","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"functions.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexProtocol"},{"text":" protocol exposes the methods and properties of an underlying ","type":"text"},{"code":"GStaticMutex","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"The default implementation of these can be found in the protocol extension below.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"For a concrete class that implements these methods and properties, see ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Alternatively, use ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" as a lighweight, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unowned"},{"type":"text","text":" reference if you already have an instance you just want to use."}]}]}],"metadata":{"role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"symbolKind":"protocol","roleHeading":"Protocol","externalID":"s:4GLib19StaticMutexProtocolP","title":"StaticMutexProtocol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"StaticMutexProtocol"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"StaticMutexProtocol","kind":"identifier"}]},"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Instance-Properties","title":"Instance Properties","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexProtocol\/mutex","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexProtocol\/mutexImpl"]},{"generated":true,"anchor":"Instance-Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexProtocol\/free()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexProtocol\/getMutexImpl()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexProtocol\/init_()"],"title":"Instance Methods"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/staticmutexprotocol"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexProtocol","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"abstract":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" works like a "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","title":"GLib","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib","abstract":[]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/Mutex":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/mutex","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Mutex","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","i